Graph Theory Concepts Applied:

Nodes (States): Represent the different stages in the workflow.
Edges (Transitions): Directed transitions from one state to another.
Connectivity: All states (except the initial state) must have at least one incoming transition to ensure a fully connected workflow, without isolated states.
